  "title" : "IntelliJ shows method parameter hints on usage - How to disable it",
  "body" : "<p>I am new to IntelliJ and recently updated to <strong>IntelliJ-2016.3</strong>.<br />\nIn the editor for Java code, it shows the method signature upon usage. How do I disable this feature?</p>\n<p>Here's an example of a method's signature and its call site:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/qMA5c.jpg\" alt=\"1\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Method call:</strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/ZZXXy.jpg\" alt=\"2\" /></p>\n<p>This behavior was not there in 2016.1.4 version. I am seeing this after update.</p>\n"
